node.text:
#Repost @RedBullRacing: Racing is in our DNA and we love what we do! 😁🏁 Here's to the next 3️⃣0️⃣0️⃣ #ChargeOn 🤘

📹@F1 

#👐 #TurkishGP #Formula1 #RedBullRacing #TopMoments #F1 #RedBull #GivesYouWings

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner on July 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
Pleased you’re home @maxverstappen1. Rest up and let’s prepare for the final race before the summer break! 

#Repost @maxverstappen1: ‘Good to be back home 👌’ 

#redbullracing #F1 #BritishGP

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Silverstone Circuit. May be an image of road.

node.text:
Whilst the rivalry is intense on track for the Championship, highly charged emotions should never cross the line into racist abuse. 

We have a zero tolerance approach to racist behaviour within our Team and I personally feel strongly that those responsible for this sort of abuse should be held to account. 

We will continue to support the FIA and F1 in order to eradicate this from our sport.

#F1 #RedBullRacing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Silverstone with @maxverstappen1, and @redbullracing. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Very pleased to say that @maxverstappen1 has been released from hospital this evening. 

#Repost @redbullracing: ‘Following a first lap incident at Copse Corner between Max Verstappen and Lewis Hamilton at the British Grand Prix, we can confirm that Max Verstappen walked away from his car and was immediately taken to Silverstone Circuit Medical Centre.
 
Following an assessment by the trackside doctors at Silverstone Circuit Medical Centre, Max was taken by helicopter to Coventry Hospital for further tests and observation.
 
We are pleased to confirm that Max was released from hospital at 22:00 this evening, following a thorough medical examination, without any major injuries.
 
Max and the Team would like to thank the trackside Marshalls and medical staff for their exceptional care both on-site at Silverstone and in Coventry Hospital.’ 

#F1 #RedBullRacing #BritishGP

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Silverstone Circuit with @maxverstappen1, and @redbullracing. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Our result today is that @MaxVerstappen1 is ok and was able to walk away from the car, despite being taken to hospital for precautionary checks where he currently remains for observation. It is an incredibly difficult way to end the #BritishGP weekend. 

I have reviewed the footage many times and still cannot help but feel that putting a wheel up the inside at Copse, one of the fastest corners in this World Championship, was ill-judged and a huge risk by Lewis to both drivers. He was not significantly alongside Max as you can see from the point of contact, Lewis’ front left to Max’s right rear and the move was never on, resulting in a 51G impact for Max. We are in contact with Max and Jos and will provide an update later.

For @schecoperez it was not an easy afternoon as his progress through the field was hindered after getting stuck in a DRS chain. We still have a slim lead in both championships and you can be sure that once we have had time to reflect on today, all this weekend will do is add fire to our Championship fight.

#RedBullRacing #F1 #Silverstone

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Silverstone Circuit with @maxverstappen1, and @redbullracing. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
Our first pole position at Silverstone since 2011 thanks to an impressive #F1Sprint by @MaxVerstappen1 to win the first ever sprint qualifying race, a result that breaks the Mercedes nine-year pole position streak here.

The race start was crucial for us and Max got a great launch off the line to gain the lead that he ultimately maintained to the finish. You can see that there was very little between the front of the field today and it should make for a great battle tomorrow. 

It’s just a shame not to have @SChecoPerez up there as well following his high-speed spin, but with temperatures set to soar at Silverstone tomorrow, he’ll be doing everything to progress as far as he can through the field.

#redbullracing #F1 #BritishGP

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Christian Horner on July 16, 2021 tagging @maxverstappen1, @redbullracing, and @schecoperez. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'HONDA HONDA JAK'.

node.text:
There's no place like Silverstone and it's great to see the fans back for this weekend as we try a different format with @F1 with two races, a Friday night qualifying and plenty of action. 

It will be interesting to see how P2 for @maxverstappen1 and P5 for @schecoperez in this evening's quali plays out in the sprint race tomorrow, and ultimately then where they will start Sunday's race. 

Last year we were a second back and now we're within seven hundredths of a second from pole position which shows the great progress we have made this season.

#BritishGP #F1 #RedBullRacing

Photo by Christian Horner on July 16, 2021. May be an image of standing.
Photo shared by Christian Horner on July 04, 2021 tagging @maxverstappen1. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Triple delight for @MaxVerstappen1 and the Team as we take our third win in 15 days to extend our Championship leads! 🏆👏

It was a tremendous drive from Max, leading from start to finish to take his first @F1 Grand Slam and maximising the result with the extra point for fastest lap. 

A trickier day for @SChecoPerez who made a good recovery to take P6 in the end after a few incidents through the race. Now we must all keep pushing and take this momentum to Silverstone! 

#redbullracing #F1 #redbullring

node.text:
The streak continues! 👏 3 pole positions in a row for @MaxVerstappen1 and with @SChecoPerez up there in P3, it's a great quali for the Team today! 

It was an incredible noise from the fans here at the @RedBull Ring when Max took pole. It's so great to have them back here this weekend and hopefully we can bring home an #AustrianGP result for us all to celebrate. 

#RedBullRacing #F1 #RedBullRing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Red Bull Ring. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
It is great to see the fans back at the @RedBull Ring as we prepare to go again this weekend for the #AustrianGP! 🇦🇹

A positive day back on track, as we went through some @pirelli_motorsport prototype tyre tests, which went well, while we got back up to speed.

#redbullracing #F1 #RedBullRing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Christian Horner on June 27, 2021 tagging @maxverstappen1, @redbullracing, and @redbullaustria. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
A clinical drive and victory by @MaxVerstappen1 to secure our third win at the @RedBull Ring, increase our Championship leads and make it four wins in a row! 🏆🇦🇹 @redbullracing #StyrianGP

Unfortunately a rare mistake in the pits meant @SChecoPerez missed out on a podium on what was otherwise a perfect weekend for the Team. Now we come back next week, to do it all again! Helmut might have dried out by then as well... 😅

#RedBullRacing #F1 #RedBullRing

node.text:
A first pole position at the @RedBull Ring for us and @MaxVerstappen1! 😁🇦🇹 He looked supreme today, with both of his laps in Q3 good enough for P1, securing back-to-back poles for the first time in his career. 

It'll be a P4 start for @schecoperez tomorrow as well, which puts us in a strong position for the #StyrianGP. It's never easy, it will be tight, but today puts us in position to continue the momentum we've built over the last few races. 

#RedBullRacing #givesyouwings #F1 #RedBullRing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christian Horner in Red Bull Ring with @redbullracing, and @schecoperez.

node.text:
Back on @RedBull’s home soil as we look to continue the great momentum we’ve had over the last few races. 🇦🇹

Overall, it was a positive first day on track as both drivers got plenty of mileage under their belts ahead of what promises to be a close battle at the front. #StyrianGP 

#RedBullRacing #F1 #RedBullRing #Austria
